     Kessara glanced at the tribe of women, and Ayla know, if Kessara was in here human form, she would be frowning. &lt;&lt;Do they not have a Queen?&gt;&gt; she asked. <br>
   &quot;I do not know,&quot; Ayla answered, &quot;but they are a fairly new tribe. Though I do not doubt the gods will hear there victory cries soon. They will be a wonderful tribe.&quot;<br>
   Kessara glared at her impatiently. &lt;&lt;You do not even guard these women.&gt;&gt;<br>
    &quot;No,&quot; Alya allowed,&quot;I am not of their tribe, but I am guardian of all women. Now be quiet, so I may hear.&quot;<br>
   A woman in the middle of the crowd raise her hands to silence the tribe, and spoke, while Ayla listened intently.<br>
